# Panel Component Rule

The [Panel.vue](mdc:src/components/ui/Panel/Panel.vue) component follows shadcn-vue conventions:

- Single File Component (SFC) in `src/components/ui/Panel`.
- Used for displaying content within a styled panel container.
- Accepts `spacing` (`medium` | `small`), `noShadow`, `asChild`, and `class` props.
- Uses Tailwind CSS for styling and utility classes.
- Wraps content in a [Surface.vue](mdc:src/components/ui/Surface.vue) component for consistent background, border, and shadow.
- Uses `Primitive` from radix-vue for polymorphic rendering.

For container best practices, see the [shadcn-vue Card documentation](mdc:https:/www.shadcn-vue.com/docs/components/card) as a reference.





